        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 3:55PM CDT by NWS Tallahassee FL</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Geneva, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kellys Crossroads, Tendil Crossing, Geneva, Black, Geneva Municipal
A/P, Holland Crossroads, Noma, Hendrix Crossroad, Cobb Crossroads,
Smith Crossroads, Izagora, New Hope, Noma Junction, Somerset, Miller
Crossroads, Fadette, Eunola, Barker Store, Bethlehem, and High Bluff.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
